text: I do nickname loved ones on occasion. I call my brother "Go". It makes many commands much shorter yet still remain personal "Go away".
Two metal things DO NOT fucking make music together. Learn how to use a knife & fork without cutting one with the other.
People shake hands so that they can gauge each others gripping strength in case they need help lifting things.
My large motor skills have always been way beyond my peers so they loved it when I struggled with my jacket. Stupid jock, cant work a zipper
I realized around 9-10 that there was something wrong with my small motor skills, everyone else had long masted zippers.
I don't write much better than I did when I was 8. Back then people were impressed by my handwriting. I gave up trying to improve around 13.
"Is that your signature?" "Yes." "Are you sure?" "Yes!" "Ummm, okay" "You sure you don't wan't to sign again?" "ugh."
So I set out to devour everything comedic I could get. I've put in more hours becoming mildly funny than most successful stand ups.
I didn't actually have a NT sense of humor for a long time. I was a clown & desperately wanted to be funny but wasn't. cont...
Legos, zippers & shoelaces were invented by some freakishly skilled Asian dude with small hands.
Hands & fingers, how the fuck am I supposed to work these things? They apparently aren't meant to go near my eyes. Is there a manual?
I enjoy my music more when my eardrums hurt & I'm being shoved around by a few hundred sweaty people. So yes, I'd love to go to a concert.
People say hello so they can gauge each other's emotional state; so they know if 1 of them is going to kill the other over the other's wife.
No brain, the Jamba Juice guy doesn't want to know the capital of Sweden, figure out what smoothie we want. "Did you know the capital.." ugh
